<ext_description linkend="Classification_assignment_mim.applied_classification_assignment">
An <b>Applied_classification_assignment</b> is a type of <b>Classification_assignment</b> that associates an instance of <b>group</b> or of one of its specializations with one or more <b>classification_item</b> instances for classification purposes.
<p>The considered group is specified with the inherited attribute <b>assigned_class</b>. The meaning of the association is specified with the inherited attribute <b>role</b>.</p>
<note number="1">The considered group may be a <b>class</b> or a <b>characterized_class</b>.</note>
<note number="2">Specific application modules address particular kinds of classification. For example, the entity <b>applied_security_classification_assignment</b>, defined in module security_classification, will be used in order to represent confidentiality level classification.</note>
</ext_description>
